-- 
2011-02-21T16:02:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/bank-al-jazira-lowers-fourth-quarter-loan-loss-provisions-75-.html
  Bank Al-Jazira ,  Saudi Arabia â€™s
smallest lender by market value, reduced provisions for bad
loans by 75 percent in the fourth quarter.  Provisions dropped to 65 million riyals ($17 million) in
the three months ended Dec. 31, from 257 million riyals a year
earlier, according to data posted on the  Saudi bourse  website
today.  On Jan. 17, Bank Al Jazira said its fourth-quarter loss
narrowed to 27 million riyals, from 266 million riyals in the
year-earlier period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
